alternatives.transcript: i had the pleasure of seeing missus palmer in the emergency department miss palmer is a sixty two year old female presenting in the emergency department with a chief complaint of shortness of breath and chest pain her vitals demonstrated elevated heart rate at one ten and a low o two saturation at ninety one percent she states that she has had trouble breathing over the past three days and she also reports that she had a cold two weeks ago including a fever a sniffle and some sneezing she states that her current symptoms are better when she is in her recliner so she's been sleeping in her recliner at night to help with these symptoms when she lays flat her symptoms are worse and her symptoms also worsen with some daily activities which would put her at an nyha classification of class two her other pertinent medical history includes a ten year history of hypertension which is well managed on lisinopril ten milligrams by mouth daily she has no allergies to medications and no history of illicit drug use no history of alcohol use and no history of tobacco use she eats a balanced diet and before her symptoms began she was exercising about two times a week at the gym and she states that she does have a support system at home and her insurance through work as an elementary school teacher her father is eighty nine and he's living in a nursing home due to his dementia and her mother passed away at eighty due to breast cancer her pertinent review of systems included fatigue and unexpected weight gain of eight pounds over the last two weeks she has been having chest pain and palpitations but no precinct could be she's also been experiencing wheezing orthopnea and dyspnea and she has lower extremity she reports that she has lower extremity edema her pertinent physical exam findings included jvd jugular venous distension bibasilar rails a displaced pmi laterally plus one putting edema in her lower extremities and normal lower extremity pulses at two plus her labs demonstrated elevated troponin and bnp and her chest x-ray demonstrated pulmonary edema and cardiomegaly her cardiac echo showed that she had diabetic or dilated cardiomyopathy with a left ventricular ejection fraction of less than thirty percent and her ekg indicated that she had sinus tachycardia at one hundred beats per minute and a right bundle branch block based on her history exam findings and diagnostic workup i believe that missus palmer has myocarditis dilated cardiomyopathy due to her recent illness this is a serious condition so i think that the best plan of action for her would include admission to the telemetry floor to monitor her vitals every two hours she can proceed with activity as tolerated and she should be monitored by nursing for strict ins and outs to daily weight ddt prophylaxis and she should receive a nasal cannula to maintain her o two saturation above ninety six percent a two d echo should be repeated and she should continue her lisinopril ten milligrams daily and she should also be prescribed furosemide forty milligrams iv over twelve hours and acetaminophen six hundred and twenty five milligrams every six hours a cmp and serial troponin should be ordered and i would like to consult with interventional cardiology radiology and infectious disease so that she can have an aicd and a crtd placed an endomyo endomyocardial biopsy can be performed she can have a media enhanced mri completed and she can have her immunoglobulins and gluco glucocorticoids evaluated if you have any questions don't hesitate to ask thank you i hope that she feels better soon
